This paper deals with the problem of discovering frequent patterns in graph databases while preserving the privacy of individuals. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on privacy-preserving data analysis and graph mining, we believe that cs.DB and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories for this paper. The other sub-categories are also relevant, but to a lesser extent.
